The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Attack on Assam train 
                                                                                                               Attack on Assam train 
                            
	Nagaon, April 10: A CRPF constable was killed and 17 persons were injured when suspected militants sprayed a passenger train with bullets in Assams North Cachar Hills district today.        
	The attackers fired from either side of the track as soon as the engine reached their level. They also lobbed a grenade that exploded after hitting the window of a coach, a passenger said.                                                                                                                                                                            
